    • Method Detail

      • forHexString

        public static Color forHexString(String hexString)
        Constructs a color with the given hexadecimal representation. The format is the same as the one used in CSS: rgb or rrggbb.
        Parameters:
        hexString - the hexadecimal representation of a color: rgb or rrggbb. Digits must be in [0-9a-fA-F]
        Returns:
        the color whose hexadecimal representation is hexString
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if hexString does not match rgb or rrggbb
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/syndata.html#color-units

      • forJavaColor

        public static Color forJavaColor(Color javaColor)
        Converts the given Java color to a color. The alpha value of the Java color is ignored.
        Parameters:
        javaColor - a Java color
        Returns:
        a color that is equivalent to the given Java color

      • mix

        public Color mix(Color that,
        double thatWeight)
        Returns the color obtained when mixing this and that. The second parameter controls the weight of that in the mixing. For example, if the weight is 0, the result is this, and if the weight is 1, the result is that.

        This method offers a simple way to enlight or darken a color, e.g. color.mix(Color.BLACK, 0.75)

        Parameters:
        that - the color mixed with this
        thatWeight - the weight of that in the mixing, between 0 and 1
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if thatWeight is not between 0 and 1 inclusive
        See Also:
        ColorMixer

      • toHexString

        public String toHexString()
        Returns the hexadecimal representation of this color, made of 3 or 6 digits: rgb or rrggbb. The format is the same as the one used in CSS.
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/syndata.html#color-units

      • toCssCode

        public String toCssCode()
        Returns a CSS code for this color. A color can have several color codes, for example #F5F5DC and beige are equivalent. It is unspecified which one this method returns.

      • toJavaColor

        public Color toJavaColor()
        Converts this color to a Java color. The alpha value of the Java color is 1 (fully opaque).
        Returns:
        a Java color that is equivalent to this color
